org.matsim.core.utils.collections

Class QuadTree<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.core.utils.collections.QuadTree<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of data to be stored in the QuadTree.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class QuadTree<T>
extends Object
implements Serializable
    An implementation of a QuadTree to store data assigned to geometric points. The expected bounds of all added points must be given to the constructor for working properly. Correct functioning of the QuadTree with elements being added outside of the given bounds cannot be guaranteed.
    At one location, several different objects can be put. An object can be put to the QuadTree at different locations. But an object cannot be put more than once at the same location.
    Author:
    mrieser

      • QuadTree

        public QuadTree(double minX,
                double minY,
                double maxX,
                double maxY)
        Creates an empty QuadTree with the bounds minX/minY -- maxX/maxY. For optimal performance, all points should be evenly distributed within this rectangle.
        Parameters:
        minX - The smallest x coordinate (easting, longitude) expected
        minY - The smallest y coordinate (northing, latitude) expected
        maxX - The largest x coordinate (easting, longitude) expected
        maxY - The largest y coordinate (northing, latitude) expected

      • getRing

        public Collection<T> getRing(double x,
                             double y,
                             double r_min,
                             double r_max)
        Gets all objects within a linear ring (including borders). Note by JI (sept '15): This method can be significant faster than calling getDisk(double, double, double) and a manual check on the returned elements for >= r_min. For randomly distributed points one can use the following rule-of-thumb: if r_min/r_max > 0.4 this method is likely to be faster than retrieving all elements within r_max.
        Parameters:
        x - left-right location, longitude
        y - up-down location, latitude
        r_min - inner ring radius
        r_max - outer rind radius
        Returns:
        objects within the ring

      • getElliptical

        public Collection<T> getElliptical(double x1,
                                   double y1,
                                   double x2,
                                   double y2,
                                   double distance)
        Gets all objects within an elliptical region.
        Parameters:
        x1 - first focus, longitude
        y1 - first focus, latitude
        x2 - second focus, longitude
        y2 - second focus, latitude
        distance - the maximal sum of the distances between an object and the two foci
        Returns:
        the objects found in the elliptical region
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the distance is shorter than the distance between the foci

      • values

        public Collection<T> values()
        Returns a collection view of the values contained in this map. The collection's iterator will return the values in the order that their corresponding keys appear in the tree. The collection is backed by this QuadMap instance, so changes to this map are reflected in the collection.
        Returns:
        a collection view of the values contained in this map.
